<p>This document describes the classification dataset loaders in GigaCheck,=
 which convert diverse external datasets into the standardized <code class=
=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal l=
eading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">TextSample</=
code> JSONL format for training classification models. These loaders handle=
 five major datasets: Deepfake, Ghostbuster, Mixset, TuringBench, and Tweep=
Fake. Each loader reads the original dataset format (CSV, JSON, text files)=
 and transforms it into a unified schema suitable for training binary or mu=
lti-class classifiers.</p>
<p>For information about the standardized output format, see <a href=3D"htt=
ps://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/3.1-data-format-specification" class=
=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:underline">Data Format Sp=
ecification</a>. For detection dataset loaders that include interval annota=
tions, see <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/3.3-detecti=
on-dataset-loaders" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:=
underline">Detection Dataset Loaders</a>.</p>
